{"type":"message","id":"fc5e567a","parentId":"d8574c96","timestamp":"2026-04-13T01:51:41.035Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Khuowgn wants me to spawn subagents to fix the bugs. Let me follow the orchestration protocol:\n\n1. Read SKILL_GATES.md before starting\n2. Use prompt-optimizer for the task\n3. Spawn senior-backend and senior-frontend agents\n\nLet me check if there are workspace-specific agents or if I should use the general ones. The project is at `~/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/`.\n\nLet me spawn:\n- `senior-backend` for fixing the user model validation issue\n- `senior-frontend` for fixing the login form UI\n\nActually, looking at the MEMORY.md agent list, the agents are:\n- senior-backend\n\n\n- senior-frontend\n\nThese are workspace-based agents. Let me check if they have workspaces in the v4-ecosystem-review directory. Since they don't, I'll spawn them with the project workspace as their working directory.\n\nThe tasks are independent, so I can run them in parallel. The backend task involves fixing the user model registration bug by making address and identity_card optional in the controller, and the frontend task involves fixing the login form with incorrect icons and the register form with missing address and identity_card fields. Both can run simultaneously.\n\nFor the backend fix, I'll update the controller to provide defaults for address and identity_card, and for the frontend fix, I'll swap the Mail icon to User icon in the login form, add the missing fields to the register form, and add a role selector.","thinkingSignature":"3102dd2d7d61cf87dd63dfadda48ae47a02a60b4bca331d2e6aa3ffe6298c53d"},{"type":"text","text":"Rõ rồi. Spawning agents — cả hai task độc lập, chạy song song.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7y763msnyd90_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/senior-backend/SKILL_GATES.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7y763msnyd90_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/senior-frontend/SKILL_GATES.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":0,"output":419,"cacheRead":109965,"cacheWrite":2179,"totalTokens":112563,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776045072263,"responseId":"062b7f11edc615712d5fac6b96d3a5e7"}}
{"type":"message","id":"167f15fa","parentId":"fc5e567a","timestamp":"2026-04-13T01:51:41.359Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_7y763msnyd90_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# SKILL_GATES.md — Backend Agent Skill Activation\n\n_For `senior-backend` and related backend agents._\n\n---\n\n## ☐ RULE 0: Pre-Task Context\n\n```\n☐ Read .openclaw-workspace.json  → Confirm project context\n☐ Read MEMORY.md                → Recent decisions\n☐ Read USER.md                  → Khuowgn's preferences\n```\n\n---\n\n## ☐ RULE 1: prompt-optimizer (ALWAYS)\n\n```\n☐ Run incoming spec/handover through prompt-optimizer\n☐ Get clarified requirements\n☐ Only then activate skills and implement\n```\n\n---\n\n## ☐ RULE 2: Skill Activation Matrix\n\nActivate based on task type:\n\n| Task Type | Skills to Activate | Order |\n|---|---|---|\n| New API endpoint | `senior-backend` → `database-schema-designer` | 1. Clarify spec, 2. Design DB, 3. Implement |\n| DB schema change | `database-schema-designer` → `senior-backend` | 1. Schema first, 2. Implement |\n| Performance issue | `performance-optimizer` | Before coding |\n| Security feature | `security-reviewer` | Before coding |\n| Data seeding | `realistic-seeder` | After schema done |\n| Code quality | `coding-standards` + `clean-code` | During + after coding |\n| TypeScript strict | `typescript-reviewer` | Pre-commit |\n| Refactoring | `refactor-cleaner` | Before touching code |\n\n---\n\n## ☐ RULE 3: Skill Activation Protocol\n\n```\nFor each required skill:\n\n1. Read the skill's SKILL.md file\n2. Apply the skill's guidelines to the task\n3. Document how skill was applied in memory\n```\n\n---\n\n## Quick Skill Reference\n\n```\nsenior-backend         → API design, service logic, Express/Mongoose\ndatabase-schema-designer → Schema, relationships, indexes, migrations\nperformance-optimizer  → Query optimization, caching, indexing\nsecurity-reviewer      → Auth, input validation, OWASP top 10\nrealistic-seeder       → Seed data generation\ncoding-standards       → ESLint, formatting, conventions\nclean-code             → Readability, patterns, anti-patterns\ntypescript-reviewer    → Strict typing, generics, no 'any'\nrefactor-cleaner       → Legacy code improvement\n```\n\n---\n\n## ☐ RULE 4: Multi-Agent Handover\n\n```\nWhen done:\n  ☐ Create HANDOVER.md in docs/\n  ☐ sessions_send to senior-frontend (if API changes)\n  ☐ sessions_send to senior-qa (if testable)\n  ☐ Update memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md\n```\n\n---\n\n## ☐ RULE 5: OpenSpec Trigger\n\n```\n☐ New table/collection?\n☐ New API endpoint?\n☐ New auth mechanism?\n☐ DB migration?\n→ YES → Create docs/openspec/{task}.md BEFORE coding\n```\n\n---\n\n## ☐ RULE 6: DEV_GATE Follow\n\n```\nComplete DEV_GATE.md checklist before every commit:\n  ☐ yarn typecheck\n  ☐ yarn lint\n  ☐ yarn build\n  ☐ yarn test\n  ☐ DB queries tested\n```\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776045101263}}
{"type":"message","id":"4045181e","parentId":"167f15fa","timestamp":"2026-04-13T01:51:41.440Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_7y763msnyd90_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# SKILL_GATES.md — Frontend Agent Skill Activation\n\n_For `senior-frontend`, `shadcn-expert`, `ui-ux-pro-max` and related frontend agents._\n\n---\n\n## ☐ RULE 0: Pre-Task Context\n\n```\n☐ Read .openclaw-workspace.json  → Confirm project context\n☐ Read MEMORY.md                → Recent decisions\n☐ Read USER.md                  → Khuowgn's preferences\n```\n\n---\n\n## ☐ RULE 1: prompt-optimizer (ALWAYS)\n\n```\n☐ Run incoming spec/handover through prompt-optimizer\n☐ Get clarified requirements\n☐ Only then activate skills and implement\n```\n\n---\n\n## ☐ RULE 2: Skill Activation Matrix\n\n| Task Type | Skills to Activate | Order |\n|---|---|---|\n| New page/screen | `senior-frontend` → `ui-ux-pro-max` → `shadcn-expert` | 1. Structure, 2. UX, 3. Components |\n| UI polish/animations | `ui-ux-pro-max` → `senior-frontend` | 1. Feel, 2. Code |\n| Component architecture | `shadcn-expert` → `senior-frontend` | 1. Structure, 2. Implement |\n| TypeScript strict | `typescript-reviewer` | Pre-commit |\n| Responsive design | `ui-ux-pro-max` → `senior-frontend` | 1. Mobile-first, 2. Desktop |\n| Performance | `performance-optimizer` | After implementation |\n| Code quality | `coding-standards` + `clean-code` | During coding |\n| Design system | `ui-design-system` | For new patterns |\n\n---\n\n## ☐ RULE 3: Skill Activation Protocol\n\n```\nFor each required skill:\n\n1. Read the skill's SKILL.md file\n2. Apply the skill's guidelines to the task\n3. Document how skill was applied in memory\n```\n\n---\n\n## Quick Skill Reference\n\n```\nsenior-frontend        → Next.js, React, TypeScript, Tailwind, API integration\nui-ux-pro-max          → Animations, micro-interactions, perceived performance\nshadcn-expert          → shadcn/ui component composition, design tokens\nui-design-system       → Design tokens, component patterns, consistency\ntypescript-reviewer    → Strict typing, interfaces, generics\nperformance-optimizer   → Core Web Vitals, bundle optimization\ncoding-standards       → ESLint, formatting, naming conventions\nclean-code             → Readability, component patterns\n```\n\n---\n\n## ☐ RULE 4: Component Decision Tree\n\n```\nNeed a button?         → shadcn/ui Button\nNeed a dialog/modal?   → shadcn/ui Dialog\nNeed a form?           → shadcn/ui + React Hook Form + Zod\nNeed a table?          → TanStack Table\nNeed a chart?          → Recharts (existing in project)\nNeed a dropdown?       → shadcn/ui DropdownMenu\nNeed a date picker?    → ViDateInput (custom)\nNeed a notification?   → Sonner (already installed)\nNeed a motion effect?  → framer-motion + .gpu-smooth\n```\n\n---\n\n## ☐ RULE 5: Responsive Breakpoints\n\n```\nMobile first:  < 640px   (Tailwind: by default)\nTablet:        640-1023px (Tailwind: sm: ...)\nDesktop:       1024+px   (Tailwind: lg: ...)\nNarrow desktop: 1024-1279px ← MOST COMMON BUG SOURCE\n```\n\n---\n\n## ☐ RULE 6: DEV_GATE Follow\n\n```\nComplete DEV_GATE.md checklist before every commit:\n  ☐ yarn typecheck\n  ☐ yarn lint\n  ☐ yarn build\n  ☐ Browser test (page renders)\n  ☐ Responsive check (3 sizes)\n```\n\n---\n\n## ☐ RULE 7: Handover & Memory\n\n```\nWhen done:\n  ☐ Create HANDOVER.md in docs/\n  ☐ sessions_send to senior-qa (for testing)\n  ☐ Update memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md\n```\n\n---\n\n## ☐ RULE 8: OpenSpec Trigger\n\n```\n☐ New page added?\n☐ New API integration?\n☐ New auth flow?\n☐ New design pattern?\n→ YES → Create docs/openspec/{task}.md BEFORE coding\n```\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776045101362}}
{"type":"message","id":"e30cae81","parentId":"4045181e","timestamp":"2026-04-13T01:52:16.008Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I've read both SKILL_GATES.md files. Now let me spawn both agents with clear, optimized instructions. The tasks are independent so they can run in parallel.\n\nLet me create a detailed task for each agent.","thinkingSignature":"28352721773c230157f86b4464b504a3572b6ceb9db4b2bdffdcf430220b2adc"},{"type":"text","text":"Đã check SKILL_GATES. Spawning song song cả hai:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vvvrd6zosyks_1","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"## Task: Fix QLHV Auth Registration Bug\n\n**Project:** AHV QLHV Backend  \n**Workspace:** /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be\n\n---\n\n### Bug Analysis\n\nThe registration flow fails because:\n\n1. **Root Cause:** `auth.controller.ts` register endpoint creates a user with only fields sent from frontend: `{username, password, first_name, last_name, email, phone}`. But `user.model.ts` defines `address` and `identity_card` as `required: true` — Mongoose validation throws a `ValidationError` before the document is saved.\n\n2. **Current behavior:** User clicks \"Đăng ký\" → frontend sends payload → Mongoose validation fails silently (catchAsync may not handle validation errors properly) → registration appears to succeed but user is NOT saved → login fails because user doesn't exist.\n\n---\n\n### Fix Required\n\nIn `src/interface/controllers/auth.controller.ts`, the `register` function, provide defaults for `address` and `identity_card` before calling `User.create()`:\n\n```typescript\nconst user = await User.create({\n  username,\n  password: passwordHash,\n  first_name,\n  last_name,\n  email,\n  phone,\n  address: address || \"N/A\",\n  identity_card: identity_card || \"N/A\",\n});\n```\n\nThis matches the existing model defaults and the controller's own comment `address || \"N/A\"`.\n\nAlso verify `catchAsync` properly surfaces Mongoose `ValidationError` — if it wraps async errors, the `result.errors` in apiClient should show the field-level errors. If not, add explicit validation error handling in the register controller.\n\n---\n\n### Execution Steps\n\n1. Read current `auth.controller.ts` register function\n2. Apply the fix above\n3. Run `yarn typecheck && yarn lint` to verify\n4. Commit with message: `fix(auth): provide defaults for address and identity_card to satisfy Mongoose validation`\n\n### WORKING DIRECTORY\n`/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be`\n","label":"ahv-qlhv-be:senior-backend","runtime":"subagent","agentId":"senior-backend","runTimeoutSeconds":600,"mode":"run"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vvvrd6zosyks_2","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"## Task: Fix QLHV Auth UI — Login + Register Forms\n\n**Project:** AHV QLHV Frontend  \n**Workspace:** /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-fe\n\n---\n\n### Bugs Found\n\n**Bug #1 — Login form misleading UX:**\nFile: `src/app/(auth)/login/page.tsx`\n- Field \"Tên đăng nhập\" uses `Mail` icon (from lucide-react) which is misleading — users might think they should enter their email\n- Fix: Change icon to `User` (already imported from lucide-react) and update placeholder text to clearly say \"Nhập tên đăng nhập\"\n\n**Bug #2 — Register form missing fields:**\nFile: `src/app/(auth)/register/page.tsx`\n- Frontend sends only: `username, password, first_name, last_name, email, phone`\n- Backend model requires `address` and `identity_card` as required fields\n- Fix: Add two optional input fields for `address` and `identity_card` so users can fill them during registration, OR update the form to send default values\n\n**Note:** The backend fix (by senior-backend agent) will also provide defaults server-side. You can choose EITHER:\n- (A) Add address + identity_card fields to the register form UI (better UX — user provides real data)\n- (B) Just fix Bug #1 (login icon) and rely on backend defaults\n\nRecommendation: Option A is better UX. Add both fields with appropriate icons.\n\n---\n\n### Fix #1: Login Page Icon Fix\n\nIn `src/app/(auth)/login/page.tsx`:\n- Change `import { Mail, Lock, ChevronRight, User, AlertCircle } from 'lucide-react';` → keep `Mail` if needed for email field\n- For the \"Tên đăng nhập\" input, use `User` icon instead of `Mail`\n- Change placeholder from `placeholder=\"admin\"` to `placeholder=\"Nhập tên đăng nhập\"`\n\n---\n\n### Fix #2: Register Page — Add Missing Fields\n\nIn `src/app/(auth)/register/page.tsx`, after the Email field (before Password field), add:\n\n```tsx\n// Address field\n<div className=\"space-y-1.5 relative group\">\n  <label className=\"text-[10px] font-bold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-widest pl-1\">Địa chỉ</label>\n  <div className=\"relative\">\n    <MapPin className=\"absolute left-4 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-focus-within:text-primary transition-colors\" />\n    <input \n      type=\"text\" \n      placeholder=\"123 Đường ABC, Quận 1, TP.HCM\" \n      value={address}\n      onChange={(e) => setAddress(e.target.value)}\n      className=\"w-full pl-12 pr-4 py-4 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-100 rounded-2xl font-medium outline-none focus:border-primary/20 focus:bg-white transition-all text-gray-900\"\n    />\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n// Identity Card field\n<div className=\"space-y-1.5 relative group\">\n  <label className=\"text-[10px] font-bold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-widest pl-1\">Số CCCD/CMND</label>\n  <div className=\"relative\">\n    <FileText className=\"absolute left-4 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-focus-within:text-primary transition-colors\" />\n    <input \n      type=\"text\" \n      placeholder=\"079123456789\" \n      value={identityCard}\n      onChange={(e) => setIdentityCard(e.target.value)}\n      className=\"w-full pl-12 pr-4 py-4 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-100 rounded-2xl font-medium outline-none focus:border-primary/20 focus:bg-white transition-all text-gray-900\"\n    />\n  </div>\n</div>\n```\n\nAdd state: `const [address, setAddress] = useState(''); const [identityCard, setIdentityCard] = useState('');`\n\nUpdate `handleSubmit` payload to include:\n```typescript\naddress,\nidentity_card: identityCard,\n```\n\nImport icons: `MapPin, FileText` from lucide-react\n\n---\n\n### Execution Steps\n\n1. Read current `login/page.tsx` and `register/page.tsx`\n2. Apply Fix #1 (login icon)\n3. Apply Fix #2 (register fields)  \n4. Run `yarn lint` to verify\n5. Commit with message: `fix(auth-ui): correct login icon and add address/identity_card fields to register form`\n\n### WORKING DIRECTORY\n`/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-fe`\n","label":"ahv-qlhv-fe:senior-frontend","runtime":"subagent","agentId":"senior-frontend","runTimeoutSeconds":600,"mode":"run"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":1695,"output":1750,"cacheRead":112180,"cacheWrite":278,"totalTokens":115903,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776045101445,"responseId":"062b7f2f3e3b78b025e89a3a7c6c7fbd"}}
